      "text": "For instance, it might be that the equivalent of the outer surface of an immune cell (which 'recognises' novel conditions) is an ethical proposition which acts as the initial receptor of all issues, and which proposes something like; \"Do what you want, unless you have an inner doubt as to whether it is ethical\". In this case, actions that don't give rise to doubt are like material that the immune system 'recognises'. If there is an inner doubt, then the specifics of the issue impinge on the system, in all their complexity; and, as with the immune system, a wide and sensitive variety of receptors will be needed to recognise them, and decide on the appropriate aspects of the network should be engaged to develop a response."
